'''Solarized''' is a [[color scheme]] designed by Ethan Schoonover.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ethanschoonover.com/solarized |title=Solarized |first=Ethan|last= Schoonover |accessdate=February 10, 2017}}</ref> It comes in two variants known as '''Solarized Light''' and '''Solarized Dark'''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://observer.com/2015/02/meet-the-man-behind-solarized-the-most-important-color-scheme-in-computer-history/ |title=Meet the Man Behind 'Solarized,' the Most Important Color Scheme in Computer History |date=February 27, 2015 |publisher=Observer |accessdate=February 10, 2017 |author=Jack Smith IV}}</ref>

<ref>{{cite web |url=https://usesthis.com/interviews/ethan.schoonover/ |author=Daniel Bogan |title=The Setup / Ethan Schoonover |accessdate=February 10, 2017}}</ref>

==History==

Schoonover began designing Solarized in 2010.

==Features==

The same palette works for both the light and dark variants.

